<subSubSection id="E5DC9FCDE263FFE8ACD63619FE89B013" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AD79CC46E263FFE8ACD63619FE89B013" blockId="8.[151,1437,1117,1540]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8ACD63619FEA5B260" bold="true" box="[151,284,1117,1143]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Discussion.</emphasis>
We place 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8ADCA361AFCCBB260" authority="Pusch, 1837" authorityName="Pusch" authorityYear="1837" box="[395,882,1117,1143]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Nassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="columbelloides" subSpecies="polonica">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8ADCA361AFD5CB260" box="[395,741,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Nassa columbelloides polonica</emphasis>
Pusch, 1837
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AFE4361AFAA1B26F" authority="Baluk, 1995" authorityName="Baluk" authorityYear="1995" box="[933,1304,1117,1144]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Pyrene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="korytnicensis">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AFE4361AFB35B260" box="[933,1164,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Pyrene korytnicensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8A8D03619FAA1B26F" author="Baluk, W." box="[1169,1304,1117,1144]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="153 - 255" refId="ref54455" refString="Baluk, W. (1995) Middle Miocene (Badenian) gastropods from Korytnica, Poland; Part II. Acta Geologica Polonica, 45, 153 - 255. [https: // geojournals. pgi. gov. pl / agp / article / view / 13663]" type="journal article" year="1995">
Bałuk, 
<quantity id="6A3E61A3E263FFE8A8A13619FAA1B26F" box="[1248,1304,1117,1144]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0673" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="1995.0">1995</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the Indo- West Pacific genus 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AD3736C5FD9EB28C" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1929" box="[374,551,1153,1179]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AD3736C5FD9EB28C" box="[374,551,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Graphicomassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on their subcylindrical last whorls, presence of a subsutural concavity, giving the adapical portion of the last whorl a slightly pinched aspect, slightly gradate spires and absence of prominent axial sculpture. The absence of an internal row of columellar denticles allows a separation from 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8A8B9368DFAC2B2F4" box="[1272,1403,1225,1251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Columbella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8A8B9368DFAC2B2F4" box="[1272,1403,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Columbella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A common feature of both Miocene species is a decollate early spire and the development of a low, spirally formed plug. The loss of the apex is known from several extant 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AF583755FC78B33C" authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1840" box="[793,961,1297,1323]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Columbellidae</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8A8683755FA25B33C" authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[1065,1436,1297,1323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Mitrella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8A8683755FB5FB33C" box="[1065,1254,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mitrella ocellata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8A8B73755FA2DB33C" author="Gmelin, J. F." box="[1270,1428,1297,1323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="3021 - 3910" refId="ref57083" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1791) Vermes. In: Gmelin, J. F. (Ed.), Caroli a Linnaei Systema Naturae per Regna Tria Naturae. Tome 1 (6). 13 th Edition. G. E. Beer, Lipsiae, pp. 3021 - 3910. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 83098  5]" type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and even in some species of the deep water genus 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AE9B3772FC91B347" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1853" box="[730,808,1334,1360]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Astyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AE9B3772FC91B347" box="[730,808,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Astyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AFD53772FF76B364" authority="Araya, Catalan &amp; Aliaga, 2016" authorityName="Araya" authorityYear="2016" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Astyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="atacamensis">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AFD53772FBCDB358" box="[916,1140,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Astyris atacamensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8A83D3772FF76B364" author="Araya, J. F. &amp; Catalan, R. &amp; Aliaga, J. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="140 - 144" refId="ref54219" refString="Araya, J. F., Catalan, R., Aliaga, J. A. (2016) A new deep-water Astyris species (Buccinoidea: Columbellidae) from the southeastern Pacific. Zootaxa, 4139 (1), 140 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4139.1.11" type="journal article" year="2016">Araya, Catalán &amp; Aliaga, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(pers. com. Marta deMaintenon, 
<date id="D978EA86E263FFE8AE0E371EFD6DB364" box="[591,724,1369,1396]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2020-11-07">7. 11. 2020</date>
). An abraded apex is frequently seen in 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8A8E0371DFA25B364" baseAuthorityName="Duclos" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1185,1436,1369,1395]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ligula">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8A8E0371DFA25B364" box="[1185,1436,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Graphicomassa ligula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8AC933739FE10B380" author="deMaintenon, M." box="[210,425,1405,1431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="43 - 48" refId="ref56227" refString="deMaintenon, M. (2016) On the identity of Graphicomassa albina (Kiener, 1841) (Gastropoda: Columbellidae). Zoosystema, 38, 43 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2016 n 1 a 2" type="journal article" year="2016">deMaintenon 2016</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1B, 1C, 1E, 1F). The genus was represented in Europe during the early and middle Miocene by several species: 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AD9B37E5FC35B3AC" authority="(Sacco, 1890)" baseAuthorityName="Sacco" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[474,908,1441,1467]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ringens">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AD9B37E5FD5EB3AC" box="[474,743,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Graphicomassa ringens</emphasis>
(Sacco, 1890)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AFD937E6FB73B3AC" authority="(Sacco, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Sacco" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[920,1226,1441,1468]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scalarata">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AFD937E6FB9CB3AC" box="[920,1061,1441,1468]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. scalarata</emphasis>
(Sacco, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8A89737E6FDB6B3C8" authority="(Sacco, 1890) (Proto-Mediterranean Sea)" baseAuthorityName="Sacco" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8A89737E6FAFBB3AC" box="[1238,1346,1441,1468]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. inflata</emphasis>
(Sacco, 1890) (Proto-Mediterranean Sea)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6AC6B7C5E263FFE8AE093782FCCCB3F7" authority="(Mayer, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Mayer" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[584,885,1477,1504]" class="Gastropoda" family="Columbellidae" genus="Graphicomassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turonica">
<emphasis id="9FB21054E263FFE8AE093782FD73B3C8" box="[584,714,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. turonica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8AE9A3781FCD4B3F7" author="Mayer, C." box="[731,877,1477,1504]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="282 - 287" refId="ref61172" refString="Mayer, C. (1869) Description de Coquilles nouvelles des etages superieurs des terrains tertiaires. Journal de Conchyliologie, 17, 82 - 88, 282 - 287. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 53431  page / 286 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1869">Mayer, 1869</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(northeastern Atlantic) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8A8FA3781FAF6B3C8" author="Sacco, F." box="[1211,1359,1477,1503]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref63411" refString="Sacco, F. (1890 b) I molluschi dei terreni terziari del Piemonte e della Liguria. Parte 6. (Volutidae, Marginellidae, Columbellidae). C. Clausen, Torino, 76 pp., 2 pls. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 45259  page / 9 / mode / 1 up]" type="book" year="1890">Sacco 1890b</bibRefCitation>
, 1891; 
<bibRefCitation id="C957B1B7E263FFE8ACD637AEFE9AB013" author="Mayer, C." box="[151,291,1513,1540]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="282 - 287" refId="ref61172" refString="Mayer, C. (1869) Description de Coquilles nouvelles des etages superieurs des terrains tertiaires. Journal de Conchyliologie, 17, 82 - 88, 282 - 287. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 53431  page / 286 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1869">Mayer 1869</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
